cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on the analysis of enterprise social networks and their use in identifying organizational charts. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper deals with the social structure of organizations and how it can be inferred from online social networks. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the retrieval of information from online social networks to identify organizational charts. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper may involve natural language processing techniques to analyze the text data in the enterprise social networks. 
5. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper may involve the use of database management techniques to store and analyze the data from the enterprise social networks.
